The paper discusses network pruning, which is a subfield of machine learning and deep learning. The focus is on reducing computational costs of neural networks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and other areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on CIFAR10 and ImageNet datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
